{"type":"message","id":"f94e9f68","parentId":"fa02842b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T23:29:17.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The subagent was spawned and is running. It will handle the web search and compilation of industry insights. The task was accepted. Since this is a cron job that runs autonomously, I should just report that the self-learning task has been triggered.\n\nActually, wait - the question says I should save to memory/学习笔记.md. The subagent won't save the file directly. Let me think about this...\n\nThe subagent will search and compile the information and output it. But the actual file writing needs to happen. Let me wait for the subagent result and then save it, OR I could give the subagent the task to also write the file.\n\nActually, the subagent run seems to be a fire-and-forget type. \n\nI need to reconsider the workflow here. The subagent is doing the research and compilation, but I'm the one who needs to persist the results to memory/学习笔记.md. I could either wait for the subagent to complete and then save its output myself, or I could spawn it with a task that includes file writing as part of its scope.\n\nSince the subagent was already launched, I'll wait for the results to come back and then handle the file saving step myself. The cron task can complete once I've captured what the subagent found.","thinkingSignature":"b8b5fdcbd8a1c63052246baf955c1987c94d0eafbc0945759248aa2d4a09d87c"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n检测到当前无活跃用户对话（最近5分钟内无用户消息），已启动自主学习任务：\n\n🔍 **正在搜索行业动态**\n- 企业数字化转型\n- 智能安防/智慧城市\n- 网络系统集成\n- IT运维服务/托管服务\n\n子Agent已启动搜索与整理工作，完成后将保存至 `memory/学习笔记.md`。\n\n如有需要可随时中断。\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1299,"output":347,"cacheRead":43981,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45627,"cost":{"input":0.0003897,"output":0.0004164,"cacheRead":0.00131943,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0021255299999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775086147057}